  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6956.65 trading just above the massive 6950 positive gamma wall (21.2B), dealers are positioned to sell this rally and provide natural resistance at current levels. The PIN regime with 139B total GEX creates a strong mean-reverting environment where dealers will mechanically buy any dips toward 6900 support and sell strength into the 6950-7000 zone. Key levels to watch are the 6950 max gamma strike acting as immediate resistance, 6900 as the next major support wall, and 6848 as the critical GEX flip level below which dealer behavior reverses.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get capped near 6950 with a pullback toward 6900 support.",
